Page_0: "Maintenance:  Do not shut off the power to any systems during business hours.  Start turning things off, and we'll turn them right back on, and it's ye own fault if ye get yourself electrocuted or mangled to death in machinery.  Turn more than one thing off, and ye can be sure we'll come running! 

Also, if I find the taffer who keeps throwing out the shorted fuses, it will be lights out for him!  When we get a bad one, keep it in the toolbox in the store room upstairs.  The foreman said I could take them home and use them for my tinkerings!  Do ye know how much copper costs these days?

- Pomok"